question:
District category contains Embassy Row, and Civic Center.
Supermarkets category contains Weis Markets, and Meijer.
The number of each Embassy Row 's Weis Markets equals 22 more than each Civic Center 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Civic Center 's Meijer equals each Embassy Row 's Meijer.
The number of each Embassy Row 's Meijer equals 19.
The number of each Civic Center 's Weis Markets equals 5 more than each Embassy Row 's Meijer.
How many Weis Markets does Embassy Row have?
solution:
Define each Embassy Row 's Meijer as C; So C = 19.
Define each Civic Center 's Meijer as B; So B = C = 19.
Define each Civic Center 's Weis Markets as F; So F = 5 + C = 5 + 19 = 1.
Define each Civic Center 's Supermarkets as Q; So Q = F + B = 1 + 19 = 20.
Define each Embassy Row 's Weis Markets as P; So P = 22 + Q = 22 + 20 = 19.
